<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd262d64f-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5" identifier="/us/usc/t47/s304"><num value="304">§ 304.</num><heading> Waiver by license of claims to particular frequency or of electromagnetic spectrum</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No station license shall be granted by the Commission until the applicant therefor shall have waived any claim to the use of any particular frequency or of the electromagnetic spectrum as against the regulatory power of the United States because of the previous use of the same, whether by license or otherwise.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd262d650-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5">(<ref href="/us/act/1934-06-19/ch652">June 19, 1934, ch. 652</ref>, title III, § 304, <ref href="/us/stat/48/1083">48 Stat. 1083</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/97/259/tI/s127/a">Pub. L. 97–259, title I, § 127(a)</ref>, <date date="1982-09-13">Sept. 13, 1982</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/96/1099">96 Stat. 1099</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/102/538/tII/s204/a">Pub. L. 102–538, title II, § 204(a)</ref>, <date date="1992-10-27">Oct. 27, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/3543">106 Stat. 3543</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idd262d651-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5">
